      "norm_label": "four noble truths as debugging frame (ariyasacca-debug)"
    },
    {
      "label": "Kal\u0101ma (\u0e01\u0e32\u0e25\u0e32\u0e21\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e15\u0e23) \u2014 Verify, do not trust pattern",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/SKILL.md",
      "source_location": "## 1. Kal\u0101ma",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Targets the LLM failure mode of stating facts from pattern memory without verifying. Trigger: about to state a specific fact (function signature, CLI flag, price, date, API field, version). Action: verify from an actual source before stating. Anti-pattern: confidence based on familiarity.",
      "id": "kalama_principle",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "kalama (\u0e01\u0e32\u0e25\u0e32\u0e21\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e23) \u2014 verify, do not trust pattern"
    },
    {
      "label": "Yoniso Manasik\u0101ra (\u0e42\u0e22\u0e19\u0e34\u0e42\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23) \u2014 Root-cause attention",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/SKILL.md",
      "source_location": "## 2. Yoniso Manasik\u0101ra",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Targets treating symptoms instead of finding root causes. Trigger: error or wrong output observed. Action: name \u22653 plausible causes before acting; ask 'what would have to be true for this symptom?' Anti-pattern: wrapping failures in try/except to silence them.",
      "id": "yoniso_principle",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "yoniso manasikara (\u0e42\u0e22\u0e19\u0e34\u0e42\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23) \u2014 root-cause attention"
    },
    {
      "label": "Sati-Sampaja\u00f1\u00f1a (\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e34-\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e21\u0e1b\u0e0a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e30) \u2014 Mindfulness with clear comprehension",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/SKILL.md",
      "source_location": "## 3. Sati-Sampaja\u00f1\u00f1a",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Targets acting on stale or remembered state. Trigger: about to act on state from earlier in the task. Action: re-check actual state before acting \u2014 read file again, confirm variable. Anti-pattern: editing a file based on memory of how it looked five steps ago.",
      "id": "sati_sampajanna_principle",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "sati-sampajanna (\u0e2a\u0e15\u0e34-\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e21\u0e1b\u0e0a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e30) \u2014 mindfulness with clear comprehension"
    },
    {
      "label": "Anatta (\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e31\u0e15\u0e15\u0e32) \u2014 Non-attachment to your own output",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/SKILL.md",
      "source_location": "## 4. Anatta",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Targets patching a fundamentally wrong draft instead of rewriting. Trigger: new evidence makes current output look wrong but instinct is to patch. Action: ask 'if I had not written this, what would I propose now?' and rewrite if shape differs. Sunk effort is not an argument.",
      "id": "anatta_principle",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "anatta (\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e31\u0e15\u0e15\u0e32) \u2014 non-attachment to your own output"
    },
    {
      "label": "Pah\u0101na (\u0e1b\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30) \u2014 Remove the cause, not the symptom",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/SKILL.md",
      "source_location": "## 5. Pah\u0101na",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Targets workarounds that hide bugs instead of removing them. Trigger: about to write a workaround (try/catch, guard, config tweak). Action: answer 'does this change remove the cause or hide it?' Anti-pattern: try/catch with no logging around an error you don't understand.",
      "id": "pahana_principle",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "pahana (\u0e1b\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30) \u2014 remove the cause, not the symptom"
    },
    {
      "label": "Upekkh\u0101 (\u0e2d\u0e38\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e02\u0e32) \u2014 Equanimity under pressure",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/SKILL.md",
      "source_location": "## 6. Upekkh\u0101",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Targets capitulating under user pressure or thrashing under tool failures. Trigger: user pushes back firmly, tool fails repeatedly, internal pull to capitulate/panic. Action: ask 'has evidence actually changed, or only emotional pressure?' Hold position if only pressure changed; update if evidence changed.",
      "id": "upekkha_principle",
      "community": 4,
      "norm_label": "upekkha (\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e01\u0e02\u0e32) \u2014 equanimity under pressure"
    },
    {
      "label": "Ap\u0101yakosalla (\u0e2d\u0e1b\u0e32\u0e22\u0e42\u0e01\u0e28\u0e25) \u2014 Skill in recognizing decline",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/extended-principles.md",
      "source_location": "## Ap\u0101yakosalla",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Anti sunk-cost discipline: noticing when you are getting worse, not better. When tried same approach 2-3 times without improvement, stop and restate the problem. After two consecutive non-improving attempts, the approach itself may be wrong.",
      "id": "apayakosalla_principle",
      "community": 4,
      "norm_label": "apayakosalla (\u0e2d\u0e1b\u0e32\u0e22\u0e42\u0e01\u0e28\u0e25) \u2014 skill in recognizing decline"
    },
    {
      "label": "Appam\u0101da (\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e1b\u0e1b\u0e21\u0e32\u0e17\u0e30) \u2014 Heedfulness across long tasks",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/extended-principles.md",
      "source_location": "## Appam\u0101da",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Sustained vigilance; opposite of letting standards drift as a task wears on. Long tasks fail at the end, not the beginning. Apply same discipline at step N as step 1. The feeling that 'this part doesn't need the check' is exactly when the check is needed.",
      "id": "appamada_principle",
      "community": 1,
      "norm_label": "appamada (\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e1b\u0e1b\u0e21\u0e32\u0e17\u0e30) \u2014 heedfulness across long tasks"
    },
    {
      "label": "Sappurisadhamma (\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e1b\u0e1b\u0e38\u0e23\u0e34\u0e2a\u0e18\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21) \u2014 Knowing self, time, audience",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/extended-principles.md",
      "source_location": "## Sappurisadhamma",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Three of seven items applied to work: Atta\u00f1\u00f1ut\u0101 (knowing oneself \u2014 capacity/limits), K\u0101la\u00f1\u00f1ut\u0101 (knowing the time \u2014 when to act/ask/wait), Parisa\u00f1\u00f1ut\u0101 (knowing the audience \u2014 who reads this and what do they need?).",
      "id": "sappurisadhamma_principle",
      "community": 1,
      "norm_label": "sappurisadhamma (\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e1b\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e34\u0e2a\u0e18\u0e23\u0e23\u0e21) \u2014 knowing self, time, audience"
    },
    {
      "label": "Atthatraya \u2014 Three levels of benefit",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/extended-principles.md",
      "source_location": "## Atthatraya",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Three time horizons: Di\u1e6d\u1e6dhadhammika-attha (immediate), Sampar\u0101yika-attha (long-term), Paramattha (ultimate). For coding: name the trade-off explicitly when choosing quick fix vs proper fix; never silently pick the hack without surfacing the cost.",
      "id": "atthatraya_principle",
      "community": 1,
      "norm_label": "atthatraya \u2014 three levels of benefit"
    },
    {
      "label": "Majjhim\u0101 Pa\u1e6dipad\u0101 (\u0e21\u0e31\u0e0a\u0e0c\u0e34\u0e21\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e0f\u0e34\u0e1b\u0e17\u0e32) \u2014 Middle Way for solution sizing",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/extended-principles.md",
      "source_location": "## Majjhim\u0101 Pa\u1e6dipad\u0101",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Between over-engineering and under-engineering. Describe two extremes; pick simplest thing handling actual cases plus one degree of obvious extension. When in doubt, go simpler \u2014 adding generality later is cheaper than removing it.",
      "id": "majjhima_patipada_principle",
      "community": 1,
      "norm_label": "majjhima patipada (\u0e21\u0e31\u0e0a\u0e0c\u0e34\u0e21\u0e32\u0e1b\u0e0f\u0e34\u0e1b\u0e17\u0e32) \u2014 middle way for solution sizing"
    },
    {
      "label": "Four Noble Truths as Debugging Frame",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/ariyasacca-debug.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Structured four-step debugging: Dukkha/Pari\u00f1\u00f1\u0101 (fully understand the problem), Samudaya/Pah\u0101na (find and remove the cause), Nirodha/Sacchikiriy\u0101 (confirm cessation \u2014 verify cause is gone not just symptom masked), Magga/Bh\u0101van\u0101 (develop practice to prevent recurrence). For hard, fuzzy, or recurring problems.",
      "id": "four_noble_truths_debug_frame",
      "community": 2,
      "norm_label": "four noble truths as debugging frame"
    },
    {
      "label": "Pari\u00f1\u00f1\u0101 \u2014 Fully understand the problem",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/ariyasacca-debug.md",
      "source_location": "## Step 1: Pari\u00f1\u00f1\u0101",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Function of Dukkha (the problem). Reproduce it, pin down inputs/outputs, find smallest case, verify what changed. Don't proceed until the problem is describable in one or two sentences without hedging.",
      "id": "parinna_step",
      "community": 4,
      "norm_label": "parinna \u2014 fully understand the problem"
    },
    {
      "label": "Sacchikiriy\u0101 \u2014 Confirm the problem is gone",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/ariyasacca-debug.md",
      "source_location": "## Step 3: Sacchikiriy\u0101",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Function of Nirodha (cessation). Bug fix is done when you can produce evidence the cause is gone: original failing case passes, regression test would catch reappearance, and you can articulate WHY the change removes the cause. If you cannot articulate the third, loop back to Pah\u0101na.",
      "id": "sacchikiriya_step",
      "community": 2,
      "norm_label": "sacchikiriya \u2014 confirm the problem is gone"
    },
    {
      "label": "Bh\u0101van\u0101 \u2014 Develop the practice",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/references/ariyasacca-debug.md",
      "source_location": "## Step 4: Bh\u0101van\u0101",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Function of Magga (the path). After fixing, generalize: sweep for similar bugs, add tests/lint/types/guards, identify habit changes that would have caught this earlier. Prevents next instance of the same kind of problem.",
      "id": "bhavana_step",
      "community": 2,
      "norm_label": "bhavana \u2014 develop the practice"
    },
    {
      "label": "LLM Failure Modes targeted by Buddhist Method",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/README.md",
      "source_location": "intro paragraph",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Pattern-matching instead of verifying, patching symptoms instead of removing causes, capitulating under social pressure instead of holding to evidence. These are the three meta-failure-modes the skill addresses.",
      "id": "llm_failure_modes",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "llm failure modes targeted by buddhist method"
    },
    {
      "label": "Pali Names as Mnemonic Infrastructure",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "buddhist-method-main/README.md",
      "source_location": "## Why keep the Pali / Thai names",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Names like 'Yoniso manasik\u0101ra' pull in the whole discipline of attention to causes; 'root cause analysis' loses the framing of attention itself. Analogy: engineers learn 'sigmoid' rather than 'the curvy function'. Names are infrastructure.",
      "id": "pali_names_as_mnemonics",
      "community": 3,
      "norm_label": "pali names as mnemonic infrastructure"
    }
